The Verkhovna Rada initiated a draft law "on the regulation of Telegram in Ukraine".

The project was initiated by People's Deputy Knyazhytskyi, and it is currently being supervised by the Committee on Freedom of Speech. Proposals for regulation of Telegram from Knyazhytskyi:

• Prohibition of distribution of illegal materials, such as pornography, glorification of fascism, justification of Russian aggression;

• Obligation to disclose the ownership structure and sources of funding of Telegram channels at the request of the National TV Council;

• If this structure and sources are recognized as non-transparent, then the platform cannot be used by state bodies and financial structures that process personal data of Ukrainians.@vallholl
